        <NOTE>Traditionally, it is Śibi [Uśīnara] who is said to have killed and 
              cooked his own son, Bṛhadgarbha, without hesitation,
              on the request of a Brahmin. See \MBH\ Suppl. 3.21:
        Łasāv ahaṃ śibinā samo nāsmi$ ||139||
        Łyato brāhmaṇaḥ kaścid enam abravīt | śibe annārthy asmīti$ ||140||
        Łtam abravīc chibiḥ | kiṃ kriyatām | ājñāpayatu bhavān iti$ ||141|| 
        Łathainaṃ brāhmaṇo 'bravīt | ya eṣa te putro bṛhadgarbho nāma eṣa pramātavya iti | 
                tam enaṃ saṃskuru |
                annaṃ copapādaya | tato 'haṃ pratīkṣya iti$ ||142|| 
        Łtataḥ putraṃ pramāthya saṃskṛtya vidhinā sādhayitvā pātryām 
                arpayitvā śirasā pratigṛhya brāhmaṇam amṛgayat$ ||143|| 
        Łathāsya mṛgayamāṇasya kaś cid ācaṣṭa | eṣa te brāhmaṇo nagaraṃ praviśya dahati 
                te gṛhaṃ kośāgāram āyudhāgāraṃ
                stryagāram aśvaśālāṃ hastiśālāṃ ca kruddha iti$ ||144|| 
        Łatha śibis tathaivāvikṛtamukhavarṇo
        nagaraṃ praviśya brāhmaṇaṃ tam abravīt | siddhaṃ bhagavann annam iti$ ||145|| 
        Łbrāhmaṇo na kiṃ cid vyājahāra | vismayād adhomukhaś cāsīt$ ||146|| 
        Łtataḥ prāsādayad brāhmaṇam | bhagavan bhujyatām iti$ ||147|| 
        Łmuhūrtād udvīkṣya śibim abravīt | tvam evaitad aśāneti$ ||148||
        Łtatrāha | tathā | iti$ ||149||
        Łśibis tathaivāvimanā mahitvā kapālam abhyuddhārya bhoktum aicchat$ ||150|| 
        Łathāsya brāhmaṇo hastam agṛhṇāt | abravīc cainam | jitakrodho 'si | 
                na te kiṃ cid aparityājyaṃ brāhmaṇārthe$ ||151|| 
        Łbrāhmaṇo 'pi taṃ mahābhāgaṃ sabhājayat$ ||152|| 
        Łsa hy udvīkṣyamāṇaḥ putram apaśyad agre tiṣṭhantaṃ 
